elements.text:
1. Arithmetic Operators
These operators perform basic mathematical operations.

Operator	Description	Example (a = 10, b = 5)	Result
    +	          Addition	         a + b	                  15
    -	        Subtraction	         a - b	                  5
    *	       Multiplication	         a * b	                  50
    /	          Division	         a / b	                  2
   %	      Modulus (remainder)	 a % b                   0
elements.originalText:
1. Arithmetic Operators
These operators perform basic mathematical operations.

Operator	Description	Example (a = 10, b = 5)	Result
    +	          Addition	         a + b	                  15
    -	        Subtraction	         a - b	                  5
    *	       Multiplication	         a * b	                  50
    /	          Division	         a / b	                  2
   %	      Modulus (remainder)	 a % b                   0

elements.text:
2. Relational (Comparison) Operators
These operators compare two values and return a boolean result (true or false).

Operator	   Description	       Example (a = 10, b = 5)	         Result
==	           Equal to	               a == b	                 false
!=	         Not equal to	                a != b	                 true
>	        Greater than	                a > b	                 true
<	          Less than	                a < b	                 false
>=	    Greater than or equal to	        a >= b	                 true
<=	     Less than or equal to	        a <= b	                 false
elements.originalText:

elements.text:
3. Logical Operators
These operators work with boolean expressions.

Operator	Description	Example (a = true, b = false)	     Result
&&	        Logical AND	         a && b	                false
||	          Logical OR               a || b                 true
!	          Logical NOT	            !a	                   false

elements.text:
4. Assignment Operators
These operators assign values to variables.

Operator	    Description	        Example (a = 10)	   Result
=	             Assignment	             a = 5	             5
+=	             Add and assign	     a += 5	             15
-=	             Subtract and assign	a -= 5	             5
*=	             Multiply and assign	      a *= 5	            50
/=	             Divide and assign	      a /= 5	             2
%=	             Modulus and assign      a %= 5	             0

elements.text:
5. Unary Operators
These operators work with a single operand.

Operator	Description	    Example (a = 5)	Result
+	         Unary plus	          +a	          5
-	         Unary minus	          -a	         -5
++	       Increment (pre/post)	++a / a++	6 / 5
--	       Decrement (pre/post)	 --a / a--	4 / 5
!	         Logical NOT	           !true	false
